==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Drawbar
<hw>Draw"bar`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Railroad)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>An openmouthed bar at the end of a car, which receives
a coupling link and pin by which the car is drawn. It is usually
provided with a spring to give elasticity to the connection between the
cars of a train.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A bar of iron with an eye at
each end, or a heavy link, for coupling a locomotive to a tender or
car.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drawbench</ent>⟦br⟧
